HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 72
BY REPRESENTATIVE ORGERON
COMMENDATIONS: Commends Sophia Patout and Layla Porter on winning the Future
Farmers of America building communities national championship award for their
Coastal Restoration Heroes program
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend Sophia Patout and Layla Porter on winning a Future Farmers of America
3 national championship competition for their Coastal Restoration Heroes program.
4 WHEREAS, Louisiana continues to experience coastal land loss at a rate of
5 approximately ten square miles per year, posing a significant threat to the environment,
6 economy, and communities of the state, including Ascension Parish; and
7 WHEREAS, Sophia Patout and Layla Porter, members of the St. Amant High School
8 Future Farmers of America Chapter, started a Coastal Restoration Heroes program in 2022,
9 focused on coastal restoration on West Grand Terre Island; and
10 WHEREAS, Sophia and Layla sought to create a program for students to actively
11 participate in coastal restoration efforts by working with Restore or Retreat Inc. to plant
12 native Spartina alterniflora (smooth cordgrass) and Avicennia germinans (black mangroves)
13 on the barrier island to support shoreline stabilization and erosion control, foster ecosystem
14 recovery and resilience, and create hurricane buffers; and
15 WHEREAS, these students not only met, but exceeded the program goals by
16 partnering with multiple restoration organizations, mobilizing student volunteers for field
17 restoration activities, and planting more than six thousand native plants by March of 2025,
18 protecting and enhancing approximately eighteen acres of backside interior saltmarsh; and
