1 WHEREAS, these efforts not only reflect a strong commitment to preserving
2 Louisiana's coast, but also serve as an inspirational model for youth engagement in
3 environmental conservation; and
4 WHEREAS, the Future Farmers of America national chapter awards program
5 recognizes outstanding chapters that show innovation in growing leaders, strengthening
6 agriculture, and building communities; and
7 WHEREAS, in recognition of their exceptional hard work and initiative, Sophia and
8 Layla won the building communities division national championship award from the Future
9 Farmers of America for the Coastal Restoration Heroes program they created.
10 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
11 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby commend Sophia Patout and Layla Porter on their
12 exceptional leadership, environmental stewardship, and civic responsibility and for winning
13 the Future Farmers of America building communities national championship for their
14 Coastal Restoration Heroes program.
15 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to
16 Sophia Patout and Layla Porter.
